article.headline: Toledo 83, St. Bonaventure 68
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Allen Pinson scored 16 points and five Toledo players reached double figures in an 83-68 win over St. Bonaventure on Saturday night. Keonta Howell and Florentino Valencia added 14 points apiece for Toledo (5-2). Kashif Payne had 11 and Justin Ingram 10. Michael Lee had 16 points for St. Bonaventure (5-3). Paul Williams had 13 and Ahmad Smith 10. Toledo led the entire game, scoring quickly on a pair of baskets by Anton Currie, his only two shots in the game. A jumper by Smith drew St. Bonaventure within one at 17-16, but a 7-0 run by Toledo in the last two minutes of the half gave the Rockets a 39-27 lead at halftime. Smith hit a jumper to cut the lead to six at the 15:09 mark, but that was as close as St. Bonaventure got in the second half.
